race.comment: JOTOPELI (3) raced on the speed and was game in defeat over 1600m at Hamilton on soft going when well supported. Drops back to a sprint and has the pace to be prominent position from the outset. Can go one better with the blinkers on for the first time. ADAMANA (5) resumes and two back was beaten narrowly at Geelong over 1443m. She jumped out well and Bates rides from a handy barrier. Decent claims if wound up. I AM TITAN (2) resumed improved with a 2L defeat at Swan Hill. It was a tough effort after settling well back in the run and presenting fitter he can hit the line hard. CRACKERJACK HATCH (9) resumes and showed enough at Hamilton on debut to consider. The jumpouts have been sharp and Coffey rides from an inside barrier. Stablemate CLISTE (7) resumes and missed a whisker at Hamilton over 1400m at his only fresh outing. Has jumped out well and has plenty of scope for improvement. May need this, but will be finishing it off.
